## Problem

Local chat sessions (chat editors and chat view panel) were not displaying progress status in the copilot status dashboard. While users could see these sessions in the chat sessions view, there was no visual indication when they were actively generating responses, unlike remote/extension-provided chat sessions.

## Solution

Enhanced the `LocalChatSessionsProvider` to track and report chat generation progress by:

- **Added progress state tracking**: Connected to chat model's `requestInProgressObs` observable to detect when responses are being generated
- **Implemented status management**: Set `ChatSessionStatus.InProgress` during generation and `ChatSessionStatus.Completed` when finished  
- **Enabled event integration**: Replaced `Event.None` with proper `onDidChangeChatSessionItems` emitter to notify the service layer
- **Leveraged existing infrastructure**: Used the existing `ChatSessionsService` pipeline to automatically display progress in the status dashboard

## Technical Changes

The implementation adds a `sessionProgressMap` to track progress state per session and subscribes to chat model observables using VS Code's `recomputeInitiallyAndOnChange` pattern:

```typescript
// Track progress for each session
private sessionProgressMap = new Map<string, ChatSessionStatus>();

// Listen for chat model progress changes
model.requestInProgressObs.recomputeInitiallyAndOnChange(this._store, (value) => {
    const newStatus = value ? ChatSessionStatus.InProgress : ChatSessionStatus.Completed;
    if (previousStatus !== newStatus) {
        this.sessionProgressMap.set(sessionId, newStatus);
        this._onDidChangeChatSessionItems.fire(); // Notify service layer
    }
});

// Include status in session items
const session: ILocalChatSessionItem = {
    // ... other properties
    status: this.sessionProgressMap.get(sessionId) || ChatSessionStatus.Completed
};
```

## User Experience Impact

**Before**: Local chat sessions showed no progress indication during response generation

**After**: 
- Status bar displays loading indicator when local chats are active
- Status dashboard shows "$(loading~spin) 2 local in progress" with real-time updates
- Consistent visual feedback across all chat session types
- Progress automatically updates when responses complete

## Implementation Details

- **Minimal changes**: Single file modified with ~85 lines added, 12 removed
- **Memory safe**: Proper cleanup of progress tracking when sessions close
- **Performance optimized**: Events only fire when status actually changes
- **Backwards compatible**: No breaking changes to existing APIs
- **Consistent session IDs**: Dynamic generation ensures tracking matches display logic

The implementation reuses existing VS Code observable patterns and integrates seamlessly with the current `ChatSessionsService` infrastructure, providing immediate visual feedback for local chat activity in the copilot status dashboard.

